      <p>If you've just become homeless, or feel that there is a risk of that happening, it's important to get the right advice
        as soon as possible. There is a range of support available, depending on your situation.</p>

      <a name="rough-sleepers"></a>
      <h2 class="h2">Support for Rough Sleepers</h2>
      <p>If you are in Southampton, you can contact the council Street Homeless Prevention Team on
        <a href="tel:023 8083 2343">023 8083 2343</a> or email
        <a href="mailto:streethomeless@southampton.gov.uk">streethomeless@southampton.gov.uk</a>
        <p>Outside of the city, if you see someone sleeping rough, and don't know how to help, you can use the national StreetLink
          service (
          <a href="tel: 0300 500 0914">0300 500 0914</a>) who will notify the local council and get them connected to the local services and support.</p>

        <h2 class="h2">In an Emergency</h2>
          <p>Call
            <a href="tel:999">999</a> in an emergency - when someone is at risk of being injured, a crime is in progress, or if you have urgent
            concerns about someone's health.</p>

          <h2 class="h2">Presenting as homeless</h2>
          <p>If you have just become homeless or are at imminent risk of becoming homeless, it’s important that you get advice
            as soon as possible from your local council, who has a duty to provide advice and assistance to anyone who may
            need it.</p>
          
            <h2 class="h2">Southampton City Council</h2>
          <p>During office hours you can contact us on telephone number
            <a href="tel: 023 8083 2327">023 8083 2327</a> or by email at
            <a href="mailto:homelessness.advice@southampton.gov.uk">homelessness.advice@southampton.gov.uk</a>.</p>
          <p>Homelessness Unit telephone hours</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Monday 8:30am to 4:30pm</li>
            <li>Tuesday 8:30am to 4:30pm</li>
            <li>Wednesday 10am to 4:30pm</li>
            <li>Thursday 8:30am to 4:30pm</li>
            <li>Friday 8:30am to 4pm</li>
          </ul>
          <p>If you are homeless because of an emergency outside of normal office hours, you can contact the council’s out of
            hours service on
            <a href="tel: 023 8023 3344">023 8023 3344</a>.</p>

